DSA = Data Structures & Algorithms

A Data Structure is a way of organizing data
so it can be used efficiently.
An Algorithm is a step-by-step process
to solve a problem


Think of it like a kitchen:

Data Structure = how you ORGANIZE ingredients
                 (spice rack, fridge, pantry)

Algorithm      = the RECIPE you follow
                 (step by step instructions)


Why does a Data Scientist need DSA?

✅ Write faster data processing code
✅ Understand how Pandas/NumPy work internally
✅ Pass technical interviews
